items.title: DOJ launches criminal investigation into Fed Chair Jerome Powell, he says
items.description: Federal prosecutors have launched a criminal investigation into Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell, he confirmed in a statement Sunday night.

items.description: At least 538 people have been killed in the anti-government across Iran, according to data published on Sunday by the Human Rights Activists News Agen...

items.title: Nearly 16,000 New York City nurses prepare to strike as contract talks stall
items.description: The largest nurses' strike in New York City history could begin on Monday morning.

items.title: WATCH:  Snowboarders carried away by avalanche in Rocky Mountain National Park
items.description: Three snowboarders were caught up in an avalanche in Rocky Mountain National Park in Colorado. No serious injuries were reported.

items.title: WATCH:  Celebrating automotive history in the motor city
items.description: Jill Woodward, the president and CEO of the Ford Piquette Avenue Plant Museum, dives into the rich automotive history in Detroit, Michigan.
